Graphical tasks

This next tasks are going to ask you to make a series of figures. For each one, I would like you to make all of them look good. Change the theme around, change the axis labels, etc. Additionally, each of these will use the reg column which has 2 factors. Change the color and/or shape of them both.

Task 1: Continuous vs.continuous plot

Create two scatterplots of logbodysize vs.trophic_position grouped by reg

First plot:
  • a 2 trend lines (method = lm), one for each reg variable
#plot 1.1
ggplot(data=bloom_df,aes(x=logbodysize,y=trophic_position,colour=reg)) + #set x-and y- values
  geom_point(aes(fill=reg),size=4,pch=21,colour='black') + #fill color with reg 
  stat_smooth(method = "lm", linetype='solid', size=1) + #fit a trendline using method= 'lm'
  xlab('Log body size') +  #label x-axis
  ylab('Trophic position')+ #label y-axis
  ggtitle('Plot 1.1 Log body size vs. trophic position')+ #add a plot title
  theme_bw() +  #change a plot theme to black and white
  theme(legend.position = 'bottom', #manually control components of the layout
        plot.title = element_text(family = "Times New Roman",  size = 18, colour="black",face = "bold"),
        axis.text = element_text(family = "Times New Roman",size=14),
        axis.title = element_text(family = "Times New Roman",size = 16, colour="black",face = "bold"),
        panel.border = element_rect(size = 1, colour = "black"),
        legend.title = element_text(family = "Times New Roman",size = 16, colour="black",face = "bold",vjust =1),
        legend.text = element_text(family = "Times New Roman",size=14),
        panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank())
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

Second plot
  • a single trend line for the whole model
#plot 1.2
ggplot(data=bloom_df,aes(x=logbodysize,y=trophic_position)) + #remove 'color=reg' to grate a single trendline for the whole model

  stat_smooth(method = "lm", linetype='solid',color='black', size=1) + #fit a trendline using method= 'lm'

Task 2: Continuous vs.categorical

The layout will be:
  • 2 panels: trophic_position and logbodysize
  • x axis: reg
  • y axis: value of trophic_position and logbodysize
Create 4 plots:
  • bar and error bars (mean and 95% conf. int.)
  • point and error bars (mean and 95% conf. int.)
  • box plots
  • raw data + point and error bars (mean and 95% conf. int.)

All these plots should have the same general layout but change the type of plot to visualize the data.

HINT: logbodysize and trophic_position need to be turned into long format

Example layout:

sample layout for task2

#turning data into a long format
#log body size
body_df <- bloom_df %>% select ('taxa','genus','species','logbodysize','reg')
body_df$measure <- 'logbodysize'
#change column name 'logbodysize' to 'value'
colnames(body_df)[4] <- "value"

#trophic position
trophic_df <- bloom_df %>% select ('taxa','genus','species','trophic_position','reg')
trophic_df$measure <- 'trophic_position'
#change column name 'logbodysize' to 'value'
colnames(trophic_df)[4] <- "value"

#combine body_df with trophic_df to create a long formatted df
long_df <- rbind(body_df,trophic_df)
long_df$measure <- as.factor(long_df$measure)
#plot 2.1
ggplot(data=long_df,aes(x=reg,y=value,fill=measure)) +
  facet_wrap(~measure,nrow=1,scales = 'free') +
  stat_summary(fun = mean, geom = "bar") +
  stat_summary(fun.data = mean_cl_boot, geom = "errorbar",color='black') +

Put them together using patchwork or ggarrange
